title: For Sale:  Glock 42: Magguts +1 spring/follower (2)
postcontent: $30 for both Two (2) Magguts spring/follower sets for Glock 42, almost new in package Here's the story: I just bought 4 of these for my new Glock 42. I also bought a Pearce +1 and a Taran Tactical +1. I was thinking I'd have +1 in my flush mags and +2 in my extension mags. Well, the Magguts in the flush mags get 7 rounds and functioned flawlessly at the range yesterday. However, the Magguts with both kinds of the extended mags DO ALLOW 8 rounds to get into the mag, but the top round is so tight that shooting the gun with a 9th round in the chamber and an 8rd mag caused so much friction on the slide that it never chambered the next round, leaving a spent shell in the chamber. I decided to put the factory followers/springs back in the extended mags (which still help in the pinky department) and keep my Magguts in the flush mags (which are great for pocket carry). I only need two of these. NOTE: I just remembered that I should add the fact that these followers are compatible with all G42 mags, including the newest "03" mags.
